edu.unito.tree

Class Tree<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.unito.tree.Tree<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>

    public class Tree<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<T>
    The class Tree is used to collect all of the tree types, and acts as a generic k-Tree.
    Author:
    Riccardo Ferrero Regis, Roger Ferrod, Luca Chironna

      • addTree

        public Tree<T> addTree(Tree<T> tree)
        Add a subtree to the current node as last child.

        The parameter cannot be null and must be different to the node itself actually the method cannot prevent the creation of cycle in the tree.

        Parameters:
        tree - The new subtree.
        Returns:
        The new tree with the subtree added.

      • addTree

        public Tree<T> addTree(Tree<T> tree,
                       int i)
        Add a subtree to the current node as child number i.

        The parameter cannot be null and must be different to the node itself actually the method cannot prevent the creation of cycle in the tree.

        Parameters:
        tree - The new subtree.
        i - The index position at which to add the new subtree.
        Returns:
        The new tree with the subtree added.

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
        Implements equality for Tree's.

        Two Tree objects are equal if they have equal value()s, the same number of children and their children are pairwise equal.
